Launch a Linux instance
SSH connect to this instance
Run the following commands: 
  sudo su - root
  yum update -y
  sudo amazon-linux-extras install -y lamp-mariadb10.2-php7.2 php7.2
  yum install httpd -y
  systemctl start httpd 
  systemctl enable httpd
  wget https://wordpress.org/latest.tar.gz
  tar -xzf latest.tar.gz
  cd wordpress/
  cp wp-config-sample.php wp-config.php
Open the wp-config.php file and add DB_NAME,DB_USER,DB_PASSWORD.
  cp -r * /var/www/html/
Open the configuration file located at /etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf. Under the /var/www/html directory line, replace AllowOverride None to AllowOverride All
  yum install php-gd
  sudo chown -R apache /var/www
  sudo chgrp -R apache /var/www
  sudo chmod 2775 /var/www
  find /var/www -type d -exec sudo chmod 2775 {} \;
  find /var/www -type f -exec sudo chmod 0664 {} \;
  systemctl restart httpd
  
   
After installing or complteing all the above steps. Now click on the 
  Elastic Block Store >> Volumes
In this section you we will See a Ebs volume which is attached to your Ec2 instacnce in which you installed all the Wordpress related softwares. 
Now Select that volume and click on 
  Actions >> create snapshot
  After snapshot is created click on 
   'Elastic Block Store' >> Snapshot
Here you will see your snapshot which you created above .
Now Select that snapshot and click on
 Actions >> Create Image (Now your image will be created)
 To see your own ami go to 
 Images >> AMIs
 Finally you can use your own Wordpress image for launching any Ec2 instance.
